{
  "text": "Because \u03b4 > 0, a off > 0, a on > 0 and 0 < \u03b7 < 1, 0 < A y (\u03b4) < 1. From linear system theory [CITATION_1] , the sequence {y(j)} j\u2208N is monotonic and asymptotically converges to y \u221e (\u03b4) = B y (\u03b4)/(1 \u2212 A y (\u03b4)). Therefore inf t\u22650 x(t) = inf j\u2208N y(j) = min {y(0), y \u221e (\u03b4)}",
